						<summary>

						<p>Below a belt of sculptures in the walls around the central shrine in the Airāvatēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>These label inscriptions may be assigned to the 12-13th century, on grounds of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>These describe the sculptures represented above them which depict the scenes from the lives of the devotees of god Śiva. Among them, a few may belong to the group of 63 Śaiva-saints.</p>						

						<p>For the details of these labels and those that are painted on the outer <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> nearby, see <hi rend="italic">A.R.E.p.,</hi> 1908, part II, para 66-67, pp. 68-69.</p>						

						</summary>
